    expect(massBalanceServiceMock).toHaveBeenCalled();
    expect(qualityServiceMock).toHaveBeenCalled();
  });
});
```

In this example, we create a spy using `jest.spyOn` for each service's method. We then define the behavior of each spy using `mockResolvedValue` to mock a resolved promise with the desired value. Finally, within your test, you can assert that the service methods have been called using `expect` statements.

Make sure to replace `'./MassBalanceService'` and `'./QualityService'` with the actual paths to your service files. Adjust the names of the service methods (`someMethod` and `someOtherMethod`) with the real method names you want to mock.

